article.headline: UMKC 97, Baker 58
article.story: KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Quinton Day scored a game-high 24 points Wednesday in leading Missouri-Kansas City to an 97-58 win over Baker at Municipal Auditorium. The Kangaroos (2-0) had three other players in double figures in the game against the NAIA Division II Wildcats, including Dane Brumagin with a career-high 22 points. Dominique Johnson had 11 and Brent Stephens added 10 for Missouri-Kansas City. Baker (5-1) took an 8-7 lead on a 3-pointer by junior Andy Hannon with 16:02 left in the first half, but Missouri-Kansas City scored the next 17 points and led 51-32 at halftime. After the Wildcats cut the lead to 54-40 on a basket by Hannon with 17:41 left in the game, the Kangaroos went on a 14-0 run to put the game out of reach. The Kangaroos took their biggest lead at 93-55 on a 3-pointer by Johnson with 4:42 left. Greg Allen led Baker with 23 points and Hannon added 11.
